message:
GDS-416 - foundation-styles
- created a general folder structure
- set up gulp to handle the heavy lifting
- added gulp tasks for scss, svg, html, linting, clean up, deployment
- created foundational mixins for breakpoints, grids, fonts
- added some foundational styles
- updated readme

GDS-495 - templating set up
- added metalsmith as a build engine, providing the ability to create a static website of the components
- create a basic config for metalsmith to achieve what we need for now to be built upon
- added in basic handlebars helpers
- added example component of `buttons` this has the structure we will be using for our components, featuring styles, js, html (hbs), model
- created a basic layout wrapper for our templates

feature/GDS-424 - global header
- added gulp task to handle compiling JS files
- updated `layout.hbs` to include new compiled JS plus init call for scripts
- created an `sr-only` mixin for easy reuse
- created global header component, html, css and js
- created a reusable `container` class for consistent centred content on pages
- various updates to settings, mixins, svgs
GDS-424 - updated with eslint, added watch function, cleaned up existing JS
Added simple script to automate the creation of component folders and files, updated the readme with description of new script

- Updated script to create either a pattern or component, also added prompts to the script to reduce the need for passing and remembering arguments.
- Updated config for metal smith to now group patterns in a collection
- Updated readme with new task information
- Moved header and footer to patterns

GDS-667 IE11 js transpiling issues
- Fixed issues with JS transpiling
- updated browserslistrc with link to browsers supported
- updated config to watch `main.js`
- updated package.js with latest babel
- added polyfill for `NodeList.forEach` this isnt covered by babel
- removed `Array.find` from utilities in favour of `.filter`
- corrected reversed styles in `header.scss`
separated build and surge commands in gulp
GDS-730: Added gulp-zip to solution to package dist folder as a HTML starter kit

- removed sass-lint in favour of stylelint
- cleaned up css to match linting rules
- added linting rules

- added regex for sass variable format, only allows lowercase a-z0-9 and single hyphens
- updated scss where there was an invalid variable name
- added new plugin for stylelint to enforce using variables for any color properties (background, color, border)
issue-35: added underline hover state to tertiary footer links

- update gulp build to correct file paths in zip file assets to enable viewing of design system without localhost
- updated config with new options

- added gulp task to inject svg to Zipped files
- fixed issue with `copyDist` function not running correctly

GDS-746 - bump versions and added release scripts
- removed dist as its not required anymore
- added version bumping script
- added version number to config
-  created multiple release scripts
- updated readme
- updated build process

- cleaned up gulp process, no need to delete startkit zip
- moved packages from `dependency` to `devDependencies`
Revert "Merge master into develop for v1.0.0 Release"
General updates for releases and changelog generations

feat: set up npm package distribution

Added to `package.json` `files` array to include only what we want to distribute, added fields `main`, `style`, `sass` with reference to the particular files.
Added fields for `repository`, `bugs` and `homepage`
Removed any js files for components that have no javascript dependancies

feat: updated package.json and readme after testing

Removed the `sass` field there were some spotty results with various importers manually including the full path to node modules works for now
readme has been updated to include more instructions on how to use the design system, internal dev instructions have been removed
removed css file that seems to have been committed by mistake
feat: updated sass imports, readme and package.json
fix: incorrect script for release methods removed `run` from `npm run publish`
feat: updated npm dependancies, checked for any issues with major updates

Bump axios and browser-sync (#386)

Removes [axios](https://github.com/axios/axios). It's no longer used after updating ancestor dependency [browser-sync](https://github.com/BrowserSync/browser-sync). These dependencies need to be updated together.


Removes `axios`

Updates `browser-sync` from 2.29.1 to 3.0.2
- [Release notes](https://github.com/BrowserSync/browser-sync/releases)
- [Changelog](https://github.com/BrowserSync/browser-sync/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md)
- [Commits](https://github.com/BrowserSync/browser-sync/compare/v2.29.1...v3.0.2)

---
updated-dependencies:
- dependency-name: axios
  dependency-type: indirect
- dependency-name: browser-sync
  dependency-type: direct:development
...
